{{As a Product Owner I want to toggle the visibility of version lozenges on the card in plan mode.}}
These are currently always shown when the card is assigned to a version.
Toggle option in menu/version panel/config TBD

From a support case:

{quote}
So, for usability, I wanted to break the Resolve and Close drop zones out into their own columns, but still have them both counted as "Done" for the purposes of the Backlog and Reports.

Also, our process currently uses the transition between Resolved and Closed as an indicator that additional (yet optional) testing has been performed. I guess this is really a process thing, surely we should just make the additional testing mandatory, or not track it at all. So we'd still like Resolved to be counted as "Done" for the Backlog and Reports, but have the option of seeing Issues transition to the 4th Closed column.
{quote}

{{original summary: As PMO, would like to create a dashboard that includes the Velocity Reports for several agile teams}}

The Agile Sprint Burndown gadget exists and we are able to create dashboard for 10 agile teams burn down charts.

We would like to do the same for their Velocity reports.  However, the Velocity report is not a gadget choice when creating a dashboard.

The following errors are appearing in the logs when trying to use GHGoToBoard.jspa:

{noformat}
2014-05-27 15:22:00,956 http-bio-8080-exec-3869 WARN captain.planet 921x5721500x4 1jg9m68 10.159.237.103,127.0.0.1 /secure/GHGoToBoard.jspa [greenhopper.service.rapid.RapidViewLocationServiceImpl] Could not get the query for rapid view 'BI Server Kanban' (16960) – skipping
2014-05-27 15:22:00,957 http-bio-8080-exec-3869 WARN captain.planet 921x5721500x4 1jg9m68 10.159.237.103,127.0.0.1 /secure/GHGoToBoard.jspa [greenhopper.service.rapid.RapidViewLocationServiceImpl] ErrorCollection[errors=[ErrorCollection.ErrorItem[contextId=<null>,messageKey=gh.rapid.board.error.nostatusmapped,params={},type=error]],reasons=[SERVER_ERROR]]
{noformat}

It looks like that "Could not get the query for rapid view" can be output in a couple of locations - given this appears to be a Kanban board from the name I suspect it's this one:

{code:java}
                // if we are a "Kanban board" then we might have a Work Sub Filter in play
                // we can only show the issue on the board if it appears on Work mode in this case
                ServiceOutcome<Query> outcome = rapidViewQueryService.getWorkModeQuery(user, rapidView);
                if (!outcome.isValid())
                {
                    logWarningUnableToRetrieveQuery(rapidView, outcome);
                    continue;
                }
                rapidViewQuery = outcome.getValue();
{code}

That calls:

{code:java}
    private void logWarningUnableToRetrieveQuery(RapidView rapidView, ServiceOutcome<?> outcome)
    {
        log.warn("Could not get the query for rapid view '%s' (%d) -- skipping", rapidView.getName(), rapidView.getId());
        log.warn(outcome.getErrors().toString());
    }
{code}

And the {{outcome.getErrors().toString()}} appears to be that second error. Perhaps not the most optimal way of displaying this given we're getting a {{messageKey}} that maps to a property of {{gh.rapid.board.error.nostatusmapped}}. This is below:

{code}
gh.rapid.board.error.nostatusmapped=This board has no columns with a mapped status.
{code}

Can you please fix up the {{logWarningUnableToRetrieveQuery}} method so that it prints some more meaningful information on {{outcome.getErrors()}}? In this case the admin will have no way of knowing what the {{messageKey}} is unless they find the property in the source.

